    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-07-24T00:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-07-24T00:50:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <head>301. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Laos</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d301fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, POL 27 VIET S. Top Secret; Limdis. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss>, Bangkok, Saigon, <gloss
                            target="#t_COMUSMACV1">COMUSMACV</gloss>, JCS, and SecDef.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Vientiane</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-07-24T05:50:00+00:00">July 24, 1967, 0550Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>433. Ref: <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> 200137Z Jul 67.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d301fn2">In this telegram, July 20, <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1"
                            >CINCPAC</gloss> recommended the expanded use of U.S./Thai and
                        U.S./South Vietnamese teams in Laos under <gloss target="#t_COMUSMACV1"
                            >COMUSMACV</gloss> control. (Johnson Library, National Security File,
                        Country File, Laos, Vol. XVII, Cables, 2/67–12/67)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>If the <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> staff officer who wrote
                        reftel will kindly raise his right hand, he can have my job tomorrow.
                        However, when he comes (and if he persuades higher authority to accept his
                        plans) he had better bring another 200,000 U.S. troops with him to “pacify”
                        the area he wants to occupy in Laos and to defend it against North
                        Vietnamese forces operating against it on short DMZ-type logistics
                        lines.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>I am disappointed that messages of this type are permitted to move in
                        official channels and receive wide dissemination. It is the sort of thing
                        which is giving marijuana a good name.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWH1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Sullivan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
